product_name: IT CosmeticsDo It All Radiant Concealer
summary: SummaryIT Cosmetics Do It All Radiant Concealer is the only clinically tested 4-in-1 serum concealer to plump wrinkles, conceal skin imperfections, hydrate dryness & brighten dull skin. With niacinamide and hyaluronic acid, it improves skin texture & radiance for all-day wear that won't settle into lines.

reviews.headline: I would love to buy this product again.
reviews.comments: The best Concealer/Makeup I have ever used, blends with yout skin and moisturizing even after removing the product.

reviews.headline: Love this product!
reviews.comments: A light application is all you need. It provides an even coverage before you apply your make-up shade. It conceals dark spots and great to cover dark circles under the eyes. I  also apply it along my nose to even out the coverage.

reviews.headline: My fave face product!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This is the perfect concealer! Dare I say the best face makeup product I've ever used?! This concealer is so good that I usually use it on my entire face. I don't find the coverage to be too heavy, and while this is marketed as a radiant product, my combo skin (leaning towards the more oily side) stays perfectly matte throughout the day. It doesn't settle in all the dry or maturing spots on my face, and it is so easy to blend out, leaving me to look effortlessly polished without trying too hard. The color has proven to be a perfect match, working just as well both in the Summer when I have a bit more color to my skin, and in the cooler months when my coloring is more fair. The only gripe I have is the packaging is not my favorite. The twist mechanism releases way too much product at once (a very little goes a long way with this!), therefore it leads to quite the mess and a waste of a lot of product.

reviews.headline: I like the product but not the packaging
reviews.comments: I like this concealer.  It's easy to blend and covers my well with one light layer. I do pair it with a color corrector because it doesn't cover the slight darkening I have under my eyes. It wears well throughout the day without needing to add powder. It doesn't accentuate my lines or cause my undereyes to get crinkly.

reviews.headline: New fav!
reviews.comments: This is my new fav due to how it blends, how it doesn't cake, the consistency, and the price! [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This has really become my new go to! The coverage is perfect, the shade fits me perfectly (the shade range is AH-MAZING) and the blend ability is out of this world!

reviews.headline: Overall a Good Concealer for Darker Spots
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Overall, this corrector/concealer did the trick to cover my dark circles and red spots on my face (right side has it on and left side does not) so I'm happy with it. I do think it could have a little more coverage and I may need to try a different shade to get the desired look I am searching for. Overall, a nice option!

reviews.headline: Okay
reviews.comments: I received this for testing and really wanted to love this concealer because the texture is creamy and the coverage is nice and buildable. It does brighten and looks radiant at first, but as someone in my late 30s, I notice creasing under my eyes pretty quickly. Even with setting powder, it tends to settle into fine lines. I think it's better suited for younger skin or areas without much texture. For me, it's just okay.

reviews.headline: Good but does settle in lines some
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I found this concealer was a little thick, coverage is pretty buildable from medium to full. I applied my moisturizer underneath my eyes first then applied the concealer using soft finger taps until it was fully blended. Despite this concealer advertising as not settling into fine lines I found that it did in fact settle into my more prominent lines, this may be prevented with a setting powder or spray on top but I did not use any to see how this concealer would wear first without it. Overall it is long lasting and coverage is good, I will continue to use and just try it with my setting powder and spray to see how it settles after that. The color I selected is the neutral medium.

reviews.headline: It truly lives up to its "Do It All" name.
reviews.comments:
I received this product in exchange for my honest review. 
IT Cosmetics' Do It All Radiant Concealer has become my new favorite. It's completely fragrance-free. The creamy formula is a dream, offering amazing blendability that melts into the skin seamlessly with a sponge or fingers.
​It provides solid medium coverage that perfectly conceals my dark circles and redness. The buildability is fantastic; it layers beautifully for fuller coverage without ever looking cakey. I absolutely love the finish—it's naturally radiant and luminous, brightening my under-eyes without settling into fine lines.

reviews.comments: The radiant concealer is very effective,I applied under my eyes and covered all the dark spots under my eyes ,also it leaves my skin very hydrating ,and the coverage last long ;the packaging is very nice and very appealing easy to carry everywhere

reviews.headline: Perfect for aging eyes
reviews.comments: This under eye concealer if you want to call it that is just wonderful. It goes on like skincare and feels like skin care feels very lightweight and covers great. Doesn't crease into wrinkles or bags under the eye. A+ in my opinion.

reviews.headline: I would buy again
reviews.comments: Really great coverage

reviews.headline: You can use a little or a lot
reviews.comments: I had the opportunity to try IT Do It All Radiant Concealer.   I love that it blends to my skin really well.  It comes with a built-in sponge, which I used to dab it on my face (but not to blend).  You twist the bottom of the stick to get more concealer on the sponge.  You can use a little or a lot, depending on preference.  It leaves my face with a healthy glow.  It feels light, not heavy or cakey.  I highly recommend this product.  I received this product for free in exchange for my honest review.

reviews.headline: Even looks great in different lighting!
reviews.comments: This one took me a minute because I had to learn how to apply it correctly.  The sponge on the end really picks up a lot of product and if you aren't careful you can have a bit of a shadowy gray cast but I was really happy with how much it brightened up my very dark under eye area and matched my foundation pretty well, the formula was very blend able.  I really liked the applicator after I got used to it and I'd really like to try in one shade lighter and one shade darker or warmer to try and get just the right touch. I looked at myself and said, well that looks great. Boom. That says it all.

reviews.headline: Love this IT cosmetics concealer
reviews.comments: To be honest the concealer I received is too dark for me to use as concealer so I've used it as foundation. It goes  on smooth and it gives me a natural look which is what I prefer. Definitely going to look for a lighter a lighter tone from their brand to use as concealer.

faceoff_positive.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I recently received the Do It All Radiant Concealer by IT Cosmetics, and I have to say, it really lives up to its name. As someone who's tested dozens of concealers over the years, I'm genuinely impressed with how well this one performs across the board.

First and foremost, the finish is beautiful — soft, radiant, and natural-looking. It doesn't lean too dewy or too matte, which makes it incredibly versatile for different skin types. I've worn it on both no-makeup makeup days and full glam, and it adapts really well in either case. What I love most is how it gives the under-eye area a brightened, fresh appearance without making it look overly highlighted or artificial.

Blending is an absolute breeze. The texture is creamy and smooth, and it practically melts into the skin. Whether I'm using a sponge, brush, or just my fingertips, it distributes evenly and seamlessly. There's no patchiness or creasing throughout the day, especially when I set it lightly with powder. For a concealer that looks this good, I was pleasantly surprised by how little effort it takes to get a flawless blend.

In terms of coverage, I'd say it's a solid medium. It covers dark circles and minor blemishes effectively, but it still allows your natural skin to come through a bit, which gives a more skin-like finish. If you're looking for a super full-coverage product, this might not be it — but for those who prefer a more natural enhancement, it's perfect.

The scent is quite neutral, which I personally appreciate. It's not completely fragrance-free, but it has a very light, clean scent that doesn't linger or irritate sensitive areas like the eyes.

Finally, I have to mention the packaging. It's sleek, lightweight, and super travel-friendly. The doe-foot applicator picks up the right amount of product, and the tube design makes it easy to toss in a bag or keep in a makeup kit. Everything about it feels well thought-out and user-friendly.

Overall, IT Cosmetics really nailed it with this one. The Do It All Radiant Concealer checks all the right boxes: great finish, easy to blend, just the right amount of coverage, and convenient packaging. I'll definitely be coming back to this everytime.
faceoff_positive.headline: Lovely Blend

faceoff_negative.comments: I received the IT Cosmetics Do It All Radiant Concealer in the shade Fairest Cool 115 in exchange for my honest review. My opinion is my own and based on my initial impressions after my first use of the product. One of the major pluses for me was that it didn't cause immediate irritation to my skin. That has happened before with other products by this brand and other brands. I really appreciate that this is fragrance free. I thought this style of applicator was a bit challenging to dispense the correct amount of product. One click gave me more than I wanted and it kept oozing out. From a distance, the product looked ok in terms of skin matching. It is a medium coverage product and covered my under eye darkness but not red spots on my skin. This is described as serum and supposed to be hydrating. I found it cakey and on the drier side, which made it hard to blend. I'm in my mid 40s and up close, this didn't look great. I thought it settled into my fine lines and made my skin look more textured. It didn't feel heavy. This product lasts on skin- when I did a swatch on my wrist, I needed makeup remover to get it off. The swatch looked a bit too warm toned for me but it worked ok as an under eye concealer. I wouldn't use this all over my face, just under my eyes. The fine print says the plumping and brightening claims were after 8 weeks of daily use. The description and name of the product makes it sound like skin will immediately look more plump and radiant. For the price point, I would not repurchase. I'd rather buy a cheaper concealer to use when I need it and skin care to address other concerns. I don't do a full make up look daily so I do not think I'll get the plumping and brightening benefits. If you do wear concealer all over your face daily, that makes this a better fit. My summary after the first wear- it's ok but not the best concealer I've tried. I didn't like how it looked close up. I wish it did a better job at covering redness and spots.
faceoff_negative.headline: No Irritation, Not My Favorite Finish
